  <p>He's at about 3x my throughput. The gap is mostly hours &mdash; he's presumably full-time with no interruptions, I'm interleaving with parenting. And he runs more concurrent agents with longer unsupervised runs.</p>

  <p>Per hour of engaged attention, I think we're close. But he deserves credit for going wider and being more aggressive with parallelism. And crucially, for sharing all of this publicly so people like me could learn from it.</p>

  <h2>Who can do this</h2>

  <p>I think the reason there aren't more people doing this is that it requires an unusual intersection:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Senior engineering skills</strong> &mdash; you need enough experience to architect systems and review AI output critically</li>
    <li><strong>Financial runway</strong> &mdash; this doesn't pay (yet) while you're building</li>
    <li><strong>Free time</strong> &mdash; or at least, fragmented time you can fill with short agent sessions</li>
    <li><strong>Genuine obsession</strong> &mdash; I basically do nothing else besides code and spend time with my family</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Steinberger has all of these from his PSPDFKit background. I have them from 15 years of full-stack work and some investments. Most developers have one or two of these, not all four. That's why the people doing this intensely are a small group.</p>

